19
00:03:27,995 --> 00:03:28,621
Yeah.

20
00:03:29,363 --> 00:03:32,924
Did Rosemary catch a cold
this past winter?

21
00:03:33,968 --> 00:03:37,233
Yes. She was running around
outside with her friends.

22
00:03:38,072 --> 00:03:40,837
She gets a terrible fever every year.

23
00:03:42,877 --> 00:03:44,777
Yeah, it was around this time.

24
00:03:45,313 --> 00:03:47,475
We had to rush to the doctor
in the middle of the night.

25
00:03:50,518 --> 00:03:53,146
Do you always carry around
pictures of her?

26
00:03:53,788 --> 00:03:56,257
Yeah. She's probably gotten big.

27
00:03:57,091 --> 00:03:58,752
She's growing, so her face

28
00:03:58,826 --> 00:04:00,954
has probably changed
during the time we've been apart.

29
00:04:02,063 --> 00:04:07,900
But I know that I'll be able to
recognize Rosemary,

30
00:04:07,969 --> 00:04:09,664
